Ok? where do I began this time around...! I had been a costumer for over a decade but it's only a once in a blue moon that I'll actually get some ribs from there.. Last time I've had ribs here was back in about 2008... They were great then... So today I decided I'll go get ribs. I traveled way across town mind you. When I walked in the place the owner he at first was talking about his relationship experience with younger women this type of talk was so uncalled for I don't need to know you're too old to keep up with younger women.. But anyway🤔  his loudness and his whole demeanor was insulting to say the least. When it was my time to step up to the counter I could not believe the way this man carried on as if I was a piece of rib and cornbread and he just wanted to slop me up and take me to "London" because YES he asked if he can 'take me to London'... I was just so embarrassed and he would not stop... So I got my two orders or ribs and carried on when I got home to try them they were horrible burnt and over cooked... Sort of like old meat you just keep reheating.... I won't throw this place under the bus just yet although he doesn't deserve my money after today but for $28.00 in New York City that's a great deal... Buyers beware inspect the meat before he throws that horrible BBQ sauce on it... Get your own sauce at home any store bought is better than there.... And if you are a lady take your man with you when you go.🤔😏
